
how will you check for openports and files in a linux machine?

lsof -i or lsof

how to check kernel messages?

cat /var/log/messages

or

cd /var/log/syslog

how to check kernel buffer size?

dmesg

or

free -m

how to run a process in background in linux?

we can either use "nohup" command as nohup command-name & 

or

run a script as ./demo.sh &

